&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a Band 5 Staff Nurse looking to help provide care to those that need it? &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have a number of Band 5 vacancies at Leasowes Intermediate Care Centre and would welcome applications from both newly qualified staff nurses and those with experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A purpose built community hospital with a 20 bed capacity, Leasowes usually caters for 18 rehabilitation beds and two end of life beds. Since the onset of the Coronavirus pandemic in March, Leasowes has been converted to an end of life facility and we take pride in providing excellent care to our palliative patients. We see to it that they are comfortable, pain free and that their dignity is maintained in the remaining days of their lives. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; The centre also caters for medically fit patients awaiting action from social services to remedy any safety needs prior to their discharge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; Leasowes is a part of Sandwell and West Birmingham NHS Trust based in Smethwick, which operates City, Rowley Regis and Sandwell hospitals along with a number of other healthcare facilities within the region. It is a friendly site with excellent opportunities for furthering your medical education, offering support for colleagues both personal and professional.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; If you care as much as we do and would like to become a part of the #SWBfamily, or alternatively would be interested in arranging an informal chat to discuss the roles further, please contact us. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:Maria Chua&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Senior Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: mariachua@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0121 612 3441&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
